properties.abstract: The popular mountain bike route through high alpine terrain is also ideal as a two-day tour with an overnight stay in the Keschhütte hut.
properties.description:
From Davos you pass through the beautiful Dischmatal to Dürrboden. Here begins what is sometimes a steep climb to the old mule track and then onto the ScalettapassFor experienced mountain bikers, the pass is 80-90% rideableThrough high-altitude Val Funtauna you follow the  single trail, which is mainly easy to ride. This becomes very steep in the final part, up to the Keschhütte.

The modern SAC-lodge is even equipped with Scandinavian-style duvets, an invitation to really unwind. The stunning panorama offers a view over glaciers and mountains. The descent through Val Tuors to Bergun is brisk. From Filisur back to Davos, the true highlights are crossing the 80-metre-high Wiesner Viaduct and the mountain path with a view of the steep Zügen Gorge.
properties.name: Destination Davos Klosters
properties.title: Scalettapass/Keschhütte
